                <head>No. 400.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cadwalader</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Turner</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 21, 1875</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 101.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 178, of the 7th ultimo,
                    concerning a declaration of war against the Liberian government by the Grebo
                    tribe of Africans, has been received and read with interest. It is regretted by
                    this Government that the mission of Commissioner Payne failed to secure an
                    amicable adjustment of the question in dispute between the Grebo tribe and the
                    Liberian government, and that hostilities were imminent.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN L. CADWALADER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
